description: Throughout this week, the Washington Examiner’s Restoring America project will feature its latest series titled “Reforming the Deep State: Reining in the Federal Bureaucracy.” We invited some of the best policy minds in the conservative movement to speak to the issues of what waste, fraud, abuse, and unaccountability exist throughout the federal government and what still needs […]
title: Yes, Trump can fire bureaucrats who block his agenda

author: Washington Examiner Staff
description: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky teased a meeting with President Donald Trump this week as he prepares for “an intense week” and a “week of diplomacy” at the United Nations General Assembly session. The supposed meeting between the two leaders comes as the U.N. begins its “high-level” week. Zelensky announced the meeting with Trump in a […]
title: Zelensky teases meeting with Trump during UN General Assembly session

author: Zach LaChance
description: The Department of Agriculture announced it will stop publishing reports on food security in the United States, which the agency said have consistently been rife with “liberal fodder.” In a press release, the USDA trashed the annual reports, which began under former President Bill Clinton, as “redundant, costly, politicized, and extraneous studies [that] do nothing […]
title: USDA ends ‘politicized’ food security reports

author: Zach LaChance
description: The Trump administration is set to advise pregnant women against taking Tylenol due to a possible link between the common painkiller and an increased risk of autism in children, according to multiple reports. The Washington Post reported on Sunday night that President Donald Trump’s planned Monday announcement on autism will include raising new concerns about […]
title: Trump administration to warn against using Tylenol due to autism risk

author: Zach LaChance
description: Sen. Rand Paul (R-KY) rebuked FCC Chairman Brendan Carr on Sunday for his comments leading up to Jimmy Kimmel‘s suspension from ABC. Kimmel’s show was suspended “indefinitely” after the late-night host falsely claimed that the suspect in Charlie Kirk‘s assassination was part of the “MAGA gang.” The comments did not go unnoticed from Carr, who suggested […]
title: Paul slams FCC chairman’s comments on Kimmel suspension: ‘Absolutely inappropriate’
